
                                            Police say they are investigating the incident that occurred on Thursday morning.
                                         CAPE TOWN - A 38-year-old man has been shot dead in Mitchells Plain. Police say they are investigating the incident that occurred on Thursday morning. A murder case has been opened. No arrests have been made. The police’s Sinathi Joni said: “A shooting incident that took place on Thursday morning in Mitchells Plain left a 38-year-old man fatally wounded.”